        {
            "date": "2010-03-18 22:19:16", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Re: BIOS shipped as binary blobs without source\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "cjwatson> any binary blobs, yes\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "(need to be pruned or source provided).\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " * bios.bin we can get from seabios (although there are known bugs with the version of seabios present in Lucid, but not in the upstream version of bios.bin)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " * vgabios we can get from vgabios (although there are known bugs with the version of seabios present in Lucid, but not in the upstream version of vgabios)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " * PXE roms we should get from kvm-pxe\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " * OpenBIOS comes from openbios.org, which is GPLv2, but not packaged for Ubuntu, see Bug #183495\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " * video.x comes from maconlinux.org, which is GPLv2, but not packaged for Ubuntu\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "So ideally, we need to:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " a) depend on seabios\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " b) depend on vgabios\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " c) package openbios, and depend on openbios\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " d) package mol, and depend on mol\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Packaging openbios and mol may not be reasonable for Lucid.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "We have been discouraged by upstream QEMU to build/run different versions of any of these ROMs from what's shipped in the upstream tarball, as those versions are the ones that are known to work well.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "kirkland", 
            "email": "kirkland"
        }, 
        {
            "date": "2010-03-18 23:36:51", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Re: [Bug 541524] Re: BIOS shipped as binary blobs without source\nAs I said, it's fine to use versions that are shipped in the upstream\ntarball;", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " I certainly don't care whether the files live in the qemu-kvm\npackage or in vgabios etc.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "  Regardless of this, though, we need to\nprovide source for them or we are infringing the licence on at least the\nLGPLed BIOS ROMs.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  Upstream QEMU is not the copyright owner for all of\nthis stuff, as far as I can tell, and does not have the authority to\nwaive our obligations.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Aside from legal obligations, we're also skating along the edge of our\nown licensing policy by not shipping source:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "http://www.ubuntu.com/community/ubuntustory/licensing.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  One might point\nout that BIOS ROMs are firmware and thus might be eligible for a\ncase-by-case exception.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  Such exceptions were only meant to be granted\nwhen the only way we could get some piece of hardware working was to\nship some bit of firmware we only had in the form of a binary blob.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  I\ndon't think anyone ever envisaged that the reason we might be shipping\nbinary blobs would be because it was too hard to build from source\naccurately, and this doesn't seem like a good basis for an exception.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I would strongly recommend building the ROMs from matching source code\n(I don't think source is really source unless we're actually building\nthe binaries from it - part of the point of shipping source is so that\npeople can make modifications, and if the source doesn't verifiably\nmatch what we're shipping then that rather defeats the point).", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  If\nyou're concerned that it might not match, then perhaps you could simply\ncompare it against a checksum after building, with a comment saying that\nthis is to ensure that they match the versions that have been QAed by\nupstream?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  I'd have thought that the sort of compilation being done here\nis using fairly static toolchain elements and thus would produce fairly\nstatic output, which would require at most minor massaging to become\nbitwise-identical to what upstream's shipping.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "On Thu, Mar 18, 2010 at 10:19:16PM -0000, Dustin Kirkland wrote:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">  d) package mol, and depend on mol\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "video.x is already in the mol-drivers-macosx package (powerpc only);", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " mol\nhas been in the Ubuntu archive since at least Hoary and I think since\nthe very beginning.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  It's not identical to the one in qemu-common,\nalthough the two files are the same size.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "mol-drivers-macosx is in multiverse, and in Debian it's in non-free.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "This is because it is licensed under the AFPL 1.2, which forbids\n\"deploying\" modified versions within an organisation without publishing\nthem, which is a restriction on privacy that we don't want in main.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  See\nhttp://www.gnu.org/philosophy/historical-apsl.html for more discussion\nhere.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  Right now, qemu-kvm's copyright file doesn't mention the\ncopyright or licence for any of the BIOS ROMs, much less this problem.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Unless there's been an APSL 2 release of MOL, I don't think we can\nlegitimately include video.x in qemu-kvm, nor depend on\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "mol-drivers-macosx.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
            "name": "cjwatson", 
            "email": "cjwatson"
        }, 
